President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan and Acting President Hwang Kyo-Ahn of South Korea to discuss North Korea's launch of ballistic missiles in violation of U.N. Security Council resolutions. Trump reaffirmed the United States' commitment to stand with Japan and South Korea against the threat posed by North Korea. He also mentioned that the administration is taking steps to enhance the ability to deter and defend against North Korea's ballistic missiles. Trump agreed with Abe and Hwang to continue close cooperation to show North Korea the consequences of its actions.